Document: VisualShaderNode
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernode.rst
Summary: Base class for all visual shader nodes.

Inherits: Resource < Object

VisualShaderNode is the base class for all nodes used in the VisualShader editor. It provides the basic structure and properties common to all visual shader nodes, such as their name, description, and input/output ports. Visual shader nodes are the building blocks of shaders created using Godot's visual shader system, allowing users to construct complex shader logic without writing code directly. Each node performs a specific operation, like mathematical calculations, texture sampling, or color manipulation, and connects to other nodes to form a complete shader graph.
---CHUNK---
Document: VisualShaderNode
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernode.rst
Summary: Base class for VisualShader nodes, providing fundamental properties and methods for shader graph construction.
Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

Base class for VisualShader nodes. This class is not related to scene nodes. It serves as the foundation for all nodes used within the VisualShader editor, enabling the creation of complex shaders through a node-based interface. All visual shader nodes inherit from this class, gaining access to common functionalities and properties required for shader graph manipulation and rendering.
---CHUNK---
Document: VisualShaderNode
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernode.rst
Summary: Describes the fundamental structure and purpose of VisualShaderNode within Godot's visual shader system.
Visual shader graphs consist of various nodes. Each node in the graph is a separate object and they are represented as a rectangular boxes with title and a set of properties. Each node also has connection ports that allow to connect it to another nodes and control the flow of the shader.
