Document: VisualShaderNode
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernode.rst
Summary: This section details the methods and enumerations for the VisualShaderNode class in Godot Engine.

Methods
Method: clear_default_input_values() → void
Method: get_default_input_port(type: PortType) → int
Method: get_default_input_values() → Array
Method: get_input_port_default_value(port: int) → Variant
Method: remove_input_port_default_value(port: int) → void
Method: set_default_input_values(values: Array) → void
Method: set_input_port_default_value(port: int, value: Variant, prev_value: Variant = null) → void

Enumerations
enum PortType:
  PORT_TYPE_SCALAR = 0 (Floating-point scalar. Translated to float type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_SCALAR_INT = 1 (Integer scalar. Translated to int type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_SCALAR_UINT = 2 (Unsigned integer scalar. Translated to uint type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_VECTOR_2D = 3 (2D vector of floating-point values. Translated to vec2 type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_VECTOR_3D = 4 (3D vector of floating-point values. Translated to vec3 type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_VECTOR_4D = 5 (4D vector of floating-point values. Translated to vec4 type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_BOOLEAN = 6 (Boolean type. Translated to bool type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_TRANSFORM = 7 (Transform type. Translated to mat4 type in shader code.)
  PORT_TYPE_SAMPLER = 8 (Sampler type. Translated to reference of sampler uniform in shader code. Can only be used for input ports in non-uniform nodes.)
  PORT_TYPE_MAX = 9 (Represents the size of the PortType enum.)
