Document: VisualShaderNode
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernode.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing default input values for VisualShaderNode ports.
Method: clear_default_input_values() → void
Clears the default input ports value.
Method: get_default_input_port(type: PortType) → int
Returns the input port which should be connected by default when this node is created as a result of dragging a connection from an existing node to the empty space on the graph.
Method: get_default_input_values() → Array
Returns an Array containing default values for all of the input ports of the node in the form [index0, value0, index1, value1, ...].
Method: get_input_port_default_value(port: int) → Variant
Returns the default value of the input port.
Method: remove_input_port_default_value(port: int) → void
Removes the default value of the input port.
Method: set_default_input_values(values: Array) → void
Sets the default input ports values using an Array of the form [index0, value0, index1, value1, ...]. For example: [0, Vector3(0, 0, 0), 1, Vector3(0, 0, 0)].
Method: set_input_port_default_value(port: int, value: Variant, prev_value: Variant = null) → void
Sets the default value for the selected input port.